## GitHub Collaboration Setup ğŸ™

### Prerequisites
- Git installed on your system
- GitHub account

### Initial Setup (After Git Installation)
```bash
# Navigate to the project folder
cd "Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story"

# Initialize Git repository
git init

# Add all files to Git
git add .

# Make initial commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: Akshay & Nishitha Love Story Website"

# Add GitHub remote (replace with your repository URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story.git

# Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

### Daily Collaboration Workflow
```bash
# Check status of changes
git status

# Add your changes
git add .

# Commit your changes
git commit -m "Description of your changes"

# Push to GitHub
git push

# Pull latest changes from collaborators
git pull origin main
```

### For Collaborators
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story.git

# Navigate to project folder
cd Akshay-Nishitha-Love-Story

# Pull latest changes
git pull origin main
```

